<rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>纽约时报 &amp;gt; 美国 &amp;gt; 政治</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/spotlight/on-politics</link><description></description><lastBuildDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 23:42:13 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>rfeed v1.1.1</generator><docs>https://github.com/svpino/rfeed/blob/master/README.md</docs><item><title>民主党人试图在中期选举中摆脱对拉丁裔的“文化迎合”</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/latino-voters-democrats-elections.html</link><description>该党正拼命地试图赢回关键摇摆群体中的一些选民。</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 23:42:13 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/latino-voters-democrats-elections.html</guid></item><item><title>国会的控制权可以贯穿缅因州北部吗？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/maine-second-district.html</link><description>该州广阔的农村地区构成了摇摆不定的第二国会选区，在 11 月份将发挥重要作用。</description><pubDate>Wed, 10 Jun 2026 15:45:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/10/us/politics/maine-second-district.html</guid></item><item><title>关于缅因州和南卡罗来纳州初选的三个问题</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/08/us/politics/maine-south-carolina-primaries.html</link><description>格雷厄姆·普拉特纳和林赛·格雷厄姆都希望能够轻松取得重大胜利。</description><pubDate>Mon, 08 Jun 2026 22:56:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/08/us/politics/maine-south-carolina-primaries.html</guid></item><item><title>在格雷厄姆·普拉特纳的争议中，缅因州参议院竞选下一步将走向何方？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/05/us/politics/maine-senate-graham-platner-democrats.html</link><description>关于格雷厄姆·普拉特纳的新披露让民主党人感到焦虑。</description><pubDate>Fri, 05 Jun 2026 21:51:59 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/05/us/politics/maine-senate-graham-platner-democrats.html</guid></item><item><title>周二加州、爱荷华州和其他地方的大型初选的六个问题</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/us/politics/primaries-california-iowa-questions.html</link><description>谁将管理加州？民主党能赢得爱荷华州吗？这就是发生的事情，以及接下来可能发生的事情。</description><pubDate>Wed, 03 Jun 2026 17:38:26 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/03/us/politics/primaries-california-iowa-questions.html</guid></item><item><title>预览加州初选和高风险的州长竞选</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/us/politics/california-primary-elections-governor-preview.html</link><description>这个深蓝色州的初选将显示选民对现状有多么愤怒。</description><pubDate>Tue, 02 Jun 2026 15:15:12 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/01/us/politics/california-primary-elections-governor-preview.html</guid></item><item><title>塔拉里科能否赢得德克萨斯州科宁的部分选民的支持？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/29/us/politics/talarico-cornyn-texas-voters.html</link><description>民主党人希望如此，但有充分的理由对此表示怀疑。</description><pubDate>Fri, 29 May 2026 21:50:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/29/us/politics/talarico-cornyn-texas-voters.html</guid></item><item><title>民主党全国委员会主席、特朗普的 18 亿美元基金和更多政治新闻</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/us/politics/dnc-chairman-ken-martin-lutnick-.html</link><description>他专注于内部政治，尽管存在战术争议，但仍建立了忠诚的基础。</description><pubDate>Fri, 22 May 2026 21:07:05 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/22/us/politics/dnc-chairman-ken-martin-lutnick-.html</guid></item><item><title>为什么乔什·夏皮罗的表现不像其他 2028 年潜在候选人</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/us/politics/josh-shapiro-pennsylvania-2028.html</link><description>这位宾夕法尼亚州州长对州内的关注与其他可能的总统候选人形成了鲜明对比。</description><pubDate>Mon, 18 May 2026 22:37:42 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/18/us/politics/josh-shapiro-pennsylvania-2028.html</guid></item><item><title>伊朗战争的强烈反对会拯救肯塔基州众议员托马斯·马西吗？</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/15/us/politics/thomas-massie-kentucky-iran.html</link><description>肯塔基州托马斯·马西区的景色。</description><pubDate>Fri, 15 May 2026 21:18:08 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/05/15/us/politics/thomas-massie-kentucky-iran.html</guid></item></channel></rss>